<paragraph id="8BC6A742FF8FFF94F1CDFEDFED97FDD4" blockId="10.[166,1225,372,719]" pageId="10" pageNumber="397">
С o m p a r a t i v e n o t e s. 
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF8FFF94F307FEDFECB3FE75" authorityName="Mackauer" authorityYear="1959" box="[529,643,373,398]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Praon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="necans">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF8FFF94F307FEDFECB3FE75" box="[529,643,373,398]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="397">P. necans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1342BBC7FF8FFF94F383FEDEECE5FE74" box="[661,725,372,399]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[166,199,1774,1796]" captionTargetBox="[470,920,995,1753]" captionTargetId="figure-11@8.[467,924,992,1761]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 8. Praon necans, Ơ: 1 — antenna; 2 — forewing; 3 — propodeum; 4 — petiole. Рис. 8. Praon necans, Ơ: 1 — усик; 2 — переднее крыло; 3 — проподеум; 4 — стебелёк." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449139" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449139/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="397">fig. 8</figureCitation>
) morphologically is very close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF8FFF94F56CFEDFEF4EFE54" authority="Stary, 1971" authorityName="Stary" authorityYear="1971" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Praon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gallicum">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF8FFF94F56CFEDFEEDAFE55" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="397">P. gallicum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE8DAB3FF8FFF94F1E4FE3FEF4EFE54" author="Stary" box="[242,382,405,431]" pageId="10" pageNumber="397" pagination="310 - 318" refId="ref7745" refString="Stary P. New aphid parasites from central Europe (Hymenoptera, Aphidiidae) // Acta Entomologica Bohemoslovaca. - 1971. - 68. - P. 310 - 318." type="book chapter" year="1971">Starý, 1971</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and differs by brown color of F1 and F2, and presence of 1 longitudinal placode on F2 (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE8DAB3FF8FFF94F0BAFE1EECD3FE34" author="Kavallieratos, N. G." box="[428,739,436,463]" pageId="10" pageNumber="397" pagination="181 - 209" refId="ref7346" refString="Kavallieratos, N. G., Tomanovic Z., Stary P. et al. Praon Haliday (Hymenoptera: Braconidae: Aphidiinae) of Southeastern Europe: key, host range and phylogenetic relationships // Zoologischer Anzeiger. - 2005. - 243. - P. 181 - 209." type="book chapter" year="2005">
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF8FFF94F0BAFE1EEC60FE35" authority="Stary, P. et al." authorityName="Kaliuzhna" authorityYear="2014" box="[428,592,436,462]" genus="Kavallieratos" pageId="10" pageNumber="400" rank="genus" status="N. G.">Kavallieratos</taxonomicName>
et al., 2005
</bibRefCitation>
). Among species of Ukrainian fauna 
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF8FFF94F5A7FE1FEEC8FE15" authorityName="Mackauer" authorityYear="1959" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Praon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="necans">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF8FFF94F5A7FE1FEEC8FE15" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="397">P. necans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF8FFF94F08FFE7FEC5EFE14" authority="Nees" authorityName="Nees" box="[409,622,468,495]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Praon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exoletum">
<emphasis id="B90D7B50FF8FFF94F08FFE7FEC17FE15" box="[409,551,468,494]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="397">P. exoletum</emphasis>
Nees
</taxonomicName>
, and differs by: 1) antenna with 15–16 segments; 2) forewing m-cu vein completely absent; 3) almost square petiole; 4) clearly concave dorsal margin of ovipositor sheath (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE8DAB3FF8FFF94F375FDBEEDAAFDD4" author="Kavallieratos, N. G." box="[611,922,532,559]" pageId="10" pageNumber="397" pagination="181 - 209" refId="ref7346" refString="Kavallieratos, N. G., Tomanovic Z., Stary P. et al. Praon Haliday (Hymenoptera: Braconidae: Aphidiinae) of Southeastern Europe: key, host range and phylogenetic relationships // Zoologischer Anzeiger. - 2005. - 243. - P. 181 - 209." type="book chapter" year="2005">
<taxonomicName id="4C79DCC1FF8FFF94F375FDBEED37FDD5" authority="Stary, P. et al." authorityName="Kaliuzhna" authorityYear="2014" box="[611,775,532,558]" genus="Kavallieratos" pageId="10" pageNumber="400" rank="genus" status="N. G.">Kavallieratos</taxonomicName>
et al., 2005
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
